revision.text:
'''Tōdaiji Yōroku''' (東大寺要録) is a temple chronicle of {{ill|Tōdai-ji|ja|東大寺|12=draft|12=draft}}, compiled in the late {{ill|Heian period|ja|平安時代|12=draft|12=draft}}. It consists of 10 volumes divided into 10 chapters.
== Overview == According to its preface, the chronicle was compiled in {{ill|Kashō|ja|嘉承|12=draft|12=draft}} 1 (1106) by a monk from Tōdaiji who wished to restore the declining temple. The editor's name remains unknown. Later, in {{ill|Chōshō|ja|長承|12=draft|12=draft}} 3 (1134), {{ill|Kangen|ja|観厳|12=draft|12=draft}} revised and supplemented the text, shaping it into the form known today. Originally a scroll manuscript, neither the original nor Kangen's version survives. However, portions of later handwritten copies, which incorporate Kangen's revisions and additional annotations, are preserved at {{ill|Daigo-ji|ja|醍醐寺|12=draft|12=draft}} (bearing a colophon dated {{ill|Ninji|ja|仁治|12=draft|12=draft}} 2 (1241)) and at Tōdaiji itself (with a colophon from {{ill|Bunmei|ja|文明|12=draft|12=draft}} 17 (1485)). Both copies are designated as {{ill|Important Cultural Properties of Japan|ja|重要文化財|1=Important Cultural Property (Japan)|2=ja|3=重要文化財|lt=Important Cultural Property|qq= (Japan)|4=ko|5=일본의_중요문화재|12=draft|12=draft}}.
The chronicle comprises chapters on topics such as foundation prayers, origins, memorial services, sub-temples, rituals, sects, abbots, tax-exempt estates, subsidiary temples, and miscellaneous matters. It incorporates many excerpts from historical materials and documents, including sources that are now lost, making it an invaluable resource for understanding Tōdaiji's history from its founding through the Insei period. Additionally, its numerous precedents served as a kind of regulatory guide within the temple.
A printed version was published by {{ill|Kokusho Kankōkai|ja|国書刊行会|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== References == * Nagamura Makoto, "Tōdaiji Yōroku" in *{{ill|Kokushi Daijiten|ja|国史大辞典|12=draft|12=draft}} Vol. 10* (Yoshikawa Kōbunkan, 1989) ISBN 978-4-642-00510-4. * {{ill|Inaba Nobumichi|ja|稲葉伸道|12=draft|12=draft}}, "Tōdaiji Yōroku" in *{{ill|Nihonshi Daijiten|ja|日本史大事典|12=draft|12=draft}} Vol. 5* (Heibonsha, 1993) ISBN 978-4-642-00510-4. * *{{ill|Hachiman Usagu Gotakusenshū|ja|八幡宇佐宮御託宣集|12=draft|12=draft}}*, edited by Shinun, 1313. * Hiraoka Sadami, "Tōdaiji Yōroku" in *{{ill|Heian Jidai-shi Jiten|ja|平安時代史事典|12=draft|12=draft}}* (Kadokawa Shoten, 1994) ISBN 978-4-04-031700-7. * Kuno Shūgi, "Tōdaiji Yōroku" in *{{ill|Nihon Rekishi Daijiten|ja|日本歴史大事典|12=draft|12=draft}} Vol. 3* (Shogakukan, 2001) ISBN 978-4-09-523003-0.
=== Related Literature === * *Tōdaiji Yōroku*, edited by Tsutsui Eishun, Kokusho Kankōkai, 1971, revised edition 2003. * *Tōdaiji Zoku (Continued) Yōroku*, supervised by Tsutsui Kanshū, edited by the same research team, Kokusho Kankōkai, 2013. * *Essays on the Ancient World of Tōdaiji: Revisiting "Tōdaiji Yōroku"*, Tōdaiji *The Great Buddha Symposium*, Vol. 14, Hōzōkan, 2017. * *Tōdaiji Yōroku Vol. 1: Tōdaiji Series*, edited by Tōdaiji Historical Research Institute, Hōzōkan, 2019. * *Tōdaiji Yōroku Vol. 2: Tōdaiji Series*, edited by Tōdaiji Historical Research Institute, Hōzōkan, 2020. == See Also == * {{ill|Tōdaiji Zoku Yōroku|ja|東大寺続要録|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Tōdaiji Bettō Shidai|ja|東大寺別当次第|12=draft|12=draft}}
